Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

When used as an isolated peptide, the C-terminus was also amidated.
1st immunogen - Name: LHEVDKDISQLTQAIVKNHKNLLKIAQY + ACET(L1)
1st immunogen - Source Molecule: envelope glycoprotein(gp21, gp46) - human T-cell lymphotropic virus type 1
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 4 doses of 100μg peptide-carrier at weeks 0, 3, 6 and 9.
Immunization - Comments: A construct where 3 copies of this peptide are linked via its C-terminus to the ε-NH2 side chain of 3 lysyl residues in a GKGKGKG template was used. The template includes a Thelper epitope from the tetanus toxin, and is acetylated at the N-teminus and amidated at the C-terminus. .
Assay - Comments: Mouse antisera was raised to a construct where this peptide is linked in a trimeric form to facilitate the interaction into a native coiled-coil structure. The antisera is shown to recognize the GP21 protein in direct and competition ELISA, as well as in the surface of HTLV-immortalized ACH cells measured by flow cytometry.

Reference - Authors: M Nakamura; Y Itoyama; M Kuroki; S Nakano; S Kondoh; S Nagafuchi; J Kira; I Ichinose; K Mitsugi; K Anzai
Reference - Title: Increase of peripheral B lymphocytes committed to the production of monoreactive and high affinity antibodies to HTLV-1 in patients with HAM/TSP.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Ten patients with HTLV-1-associated myelopathy/tropical spastic paraparesis(HAM/TSP), nine patients with non-HAM/TSP, HTLV-1 carriers and eight seronegative healthy controls were used as the source of PBMCs. B lymphocytes were enriched from the peripheral blood of HAM/TSP patients. EBV-transformed B lymphocytes that were shown to react with the HTLV-1 gag-env hybrid protein were then used to generate the mAb F31.1 by fusion with a human-mouse heteromyeloma cell line.
Assay - Comments: B lymphocytes were enriched from the peripheral blood of HAM/TSP patients. EBV-transformed B lymphocytes that reacted with the HTLV-1 gag-env hybrid protein were then used to generate the mAb F31.1 by fusion with a human-mouse heteromyeloma cell line.  This mAb was shown to specifically bind the epitope in ELISA format.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: M Nakamura; Y Itoyama; M Kuroki; S Nakano; S Kondoh; S Nagafuchi; J Kira; I Ichinose; K Mitsugi; K Anzai
Reference - Title: Increase of peripheral B lymphocytes committed to the production of monoreactive and high affinity antibodies to HTLV-1 in patients with HAM/TSP.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Ten patients with HTLV-1-associated myelopathy/tropical spastic paraparesis(HAM/TSP), nine patients with non-HAM/TSP, HTLV-1 carriers and eight seronegative healthy controls were used as the source of PBMCs.  B lymphocytes were enriched from the peripheral blood of HAM/TSP patients. EBV-transformed B lymphocytes that were shown to react with the HTLV-1 gag-env hybrid protein were then used to generate the mAb F31.1 by fusion with a human-mouse heteromyeloma cell line.
Assay - Comments: B lymphocytes were enriched from the peripheral blood of HAM/TSP patients. EBV-transformed B lymphocytes that reacted with the HTLV-1 gag-env hybrid protein were then used to generate the mAb F31.1 by fusion with a human-mouse heteromyeloma cell line.  Epitope specificity against p235-254 was demonstrated using ELISA.  The epitope-specific mAb was then shown to bind the surface of HTLV-1-infected cells by flow cytometry.  MAb F31.1 was also found to bind specifically to the 46kDa moiety in lysates from HTLV-1-infected MT-2 cells by Western blot.
Assay Antigen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Epitope - Source Organism: Baboon endogenous virus strain M7
Epitope - Comments: The epitope is also presents in Moloney murine leukemia virus (Mo-MuLV) p15env.
1st immunogen - Name: EVVLQNRRGLDLL
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Baboon endogenous virus strain M7
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: One dose of 1 mg of peptide-KLH conjugate administered in CFA followed by 0.1 mg conjugate in IFA at 2 week interval.
Assay - Comments: The reactivity was weak. Epitope specific antibodies bound baboon endogenous virus (BaEV), Moloney murine leukemia virus (Mo-MuLV) and reticuloendotheliosis virus, strain A (REV-A), and crossreacted with endogenous feline virus (RD-114), simian sarcoma virus (SSAV), feline leukemia virus (FeLV), Msson-Pfrizer monkey virus (MPMV), squirrel monkey retrovirus (SMRV) and langur retrovirus (Po-l-Lu).

Reference - Authors: P Horal; W W Hall; B Svennerholm; J Lycke; S Jeansson; L Rymo; M H Kaplan; A Vahlne
Reference - Journal: Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A
Reference - Title: Identification of type-specific linear epitopes in the glycoproteins gp46 and gp21 of human T-cell leukemia viruses type I and type II using synthetic peptides.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: HTLV-1 sera were included in a collection of 97 samples from different geographic areas and included samples from patients with adult T-cell leukemia (n= 25) and HTLV-1-associated myelopathy/tropical spastic paraparesis (n=46) and asymptomatic carriers (n=26).
Assay - Comments: The minimal epitope was deduced by correlating the relative reactivities of individual and adjacent or overlapping peptide.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Goat were immunized intramuscularly and subcutaneously in CFA (day 0) and IFA with a mixture of peptide-tetanus toxoid conjugate that included region 68-107. Assay - Comments: Incubation of the epitope with anti-SP2 peptide sera resulted in adsorption of neutralizing antibodies and a reduction in inhibition of HTLV-1-induced formation of syncytia. This minimal epitope was determined by testing overlapping peptide derived from residues 86-107 (PHWTKKPNRNGGGYYSASYSDP) of HTLV-1 envelope polyprotein. Asparagine (N) residues at position 93 and 95 were found to be important for adsorption of all three anti-peptide sera.

1st immunogen - Source Organism: Bovine leukemia virus

Immunization - Comments: Mice were immunized subcutaneously and intraperitoneally with whole bovine leukemia virus (BLV) or gp51 of BLV. Reference - Authors: M D Lairmore; A M DiGeorge; S F Conrad; A V Trevino; R B Lal; P T Kaumaya
Reference - Title: Human T-lymphotropic virus type 1 peptides in chimeric and multivalent constructs with promiscuous T-cell epitopes enhance immunogenicity and overcome genetic restriction.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Name: LLPHSNLDHILEPSIPWKSK
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 100 μg, administered at intervals of 3 weeks.
Immunization - Comments: Mice were immunized with the peptide emulsified in squalene-arlacel supplemented with muramyl dipeptide.
Assay - Comments: Antibody response was only observed when mice were immunized with the epitope linked to a peptide (KLLSLIKGVIVHRLEGVEGPSL) containing measles virus fusion protein (MVF) sequence. Sera from 4 of 5 immunized mice showed binding to the epitope alone (without MVF sequence). Antibody response against the epitope was also observed when mice were immunized with a multi-epitope construct containing the epitope, HTLV-1 peptide SP2 (residues 86-107), tetanus toxin peptide (TT), and measles virus fusion protein peptide (MVF).
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: D Pardi; J E Coligan; R B Lal
Reference - Title: Mapping of linear epitopes of the regulatory proteins of human T cell lymphotropic virus (HTLV) type II: identification of an HTLV-IIb-restricted epitope.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-lymphotropic virus 2
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-lymphotropic virus 2 (Human T-Cell leukemia virus type 2)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-lymphotropic virus 2
Immunization - Comments: Donors were a group of HTLV-2-infected Guaymi Indians.
Assay - Comments: In further studies, it was shown that seroreactivity to the epitope is linked to infection with HTLV-IIb viruses. This is reinforced by the fact that the epitope represents the carboxyl terminus of the extended TaxII protein which is a  region of protein that does not exist in HTLV-IIa viruses. By testing various populations for reactivity with the epitope, it was found that the seropositivity within the US IDU population was low (10%) and closely paralleled the US blood donor population (9.3%). Within the Amerindian populations, the Guaymi had the highest reactivity to the peptide (78.7%), followed by the Wayuu (50%), the Seminole (33.3%), the Navajo and Pueblo (22.8%), and other Southwest Indians (18.2%).

Reference - Authors: K G Hadlock; J Rowe; S K Foung
Reference - Title: The humoral immune response to human T-cell lymphotropic virus type 1 envelope glycoprotein gp46 is directed primarily against conformational epitopes.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Baba et al. (1993) J Immunol 151: 1013-1024 [PMID: 7687611].
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the monoclonal antibody was previously described in the reference cited: Hadlock et al. (1997) J Virol 71: 5828-5840 [PMID: 9223472]. Peripheral B cells were derived from a patient with HAM/TSP and human hybridomas were produced after activation of the B cells with EBV and electrofusion to heteromyeloma cells.
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific HMAb PRH-1 was used to capture HTLV-1 gp46 from lysates of the HTLV-1-infected MT-2 cell line.
Assay Antigen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: K G Hadlock; J Rowe; S K Foung
Reference - Title: The humoral immune response to human T-cell lymphotropic virus type 1 envelope glycoprotein gp46 is directed primarily against conformational epitopes.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Ralston et al. (1989) J Biol Chem 264: 16343-16346 [PMID: 2476442].
1st immunogen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the human monoclonal antibody was previously described in the reference cited: Matsushita et al. (1986) Proc Natl Acad Sci USA 83 2672-2676 [PMID: 2422659]. B cells were isolated from lymph node cells obtained from a serpositive patient with ATL and exposed to EBV (B95-8 strain). The cells were cloned by limiting dilution and the antibody producing clone 0.5 alpha was isolated.
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific HMAb 0.5 alpha bound to HTLV-1 gp46 from lysates of the HTLV-1-infected MT-2 cell line.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: K G Hadlock; J Rowe; S K Foung
Reference - Title: The humoral immune response to human T-cell lymphotropic virus type 1 envelope glycoprotein gp46 is directed primarily against conformational epitopes.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Baba et al. (1993) J Immunol 151: 1013-1024 [PMID: 7687611].
1st immunogen - Name: envelope glycoprotein
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the monoclonal antibody was previously described in the reference cited: Papsidero et al. (1992) J Clin Microbiol 30: 351-358 [PMID: 1371516]. Mice were immunized with HTLV-1 protein and boosted with recombinant HTLV-1 envelope proteins.
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific mouse mAb CLN 68 bound to HTLV-1 gp46 from lysates of the HTLV-1-infected MT-2 cell line.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: K G Hadlock; J Rowe; S K Foung
Reference - Title: The humoral immune response to human T-cell lymphotropic virus type 1 envelope glycoprotein gp46 is directed primarily against conformational epitopes.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

1st immunogen - Name: Plasmodium falciparum (malaria parasite P. falciparum)
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Plasmodium falciparum
Immunization - Comments: Anti-P. falciparum antibody-positive sera from Indonesian population were used.
Assay - Comments: The Indonesian sera showed 100% immunoreactivity to the 10-mer ( HDPPDSDPQI ), 8-mer ( PPDSDPQI ), and 7-mer ( PDSDPQI ) peptides. The 9-mer ( DPPDSDPQI ) and the 6-mer ( DSDPQI ) peptides reacted to 90% and 93% of the Indonesian sera respectively. This indicated that the shortest peptide sequence showing optimum binding was 7-mer peptide. Patients from the Philippines were also positive.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Title: Direct phenotypic analysis of human MHC class I antigen presentation: visualization, quantitation, and in situ detection of human viral epitopes using peptide-specific, MHC-restricted human recombinant antibodies.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Nagai et al. (2001) J Infect Dis 183: 197-205 [PMID: 11120926].
Assay - Comments: TCR-like Fab antibodies specific for the HLA-A2/epitope complex were selected from a large human Fab phage library using a single chain construct of HLA-A2 linked to β2m complexed with the epitope. Reference - Authors: Cyril J Cohen; Offra Sarig; Yoshihisa Yamano; Utano Tomaru; Steven Jacobson; Yoram Reiter
Reference - Title: Direct phenotypic analysis of human MHC class I antigen presentation: visualization, quantitation, and in situ detection of human viral epitopes using peptide-specific, MHC-restricted human recombinant antibodies.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Nagai et al. (2001) J Infect Dis 183: 197-205 [PMID: 11120926].
Assay - Comments: TCR-like Fab antibodies specific for the HLA-A2/epitope complex were selected from a large human Fab phage library using a single chain construct of HLA-A2 linked to β2m complexed with the epitope. Fabs T3F2 and T3E3 detected the epitope complexed with HLA-A2 on the surface of APCs pulsed with the epitope, such as murine RMA-S transfected with HLA-A2, HLA-A2+ EBV-transformed B cell line JY, or human HLA-A2+ dendritic cells. Fab tetramers showed 2-log increased staining intensity.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: Cyril J Cohen; Offra Sarig; Yoshihisa Yamano; Utano Tomaru; Steven Jacobson; Yoram Reiter
Reference - Title: Direct phenotypic analysis of human MHC class I antigen presentation: visualization, quantitation, and in situ detection of human viral epitopes using peptide-specific, MHC-restricted human recombinant antibodies.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is from the reference cited: Nagai et al. (2001) J Infect Dis 183: 197-205 [PMID: 11120926].
Assay - Comments: TCR-like Fab antibodies specific for the HLA-A2/epitope complex were selected from a large human Fab phage library using a single chain construct of HLA-A2 linked to β2m complexed with the epitope. Fab T3F2 stained HLA-A2+ EBV-transformed B cell line JY transfected with the HTLV-1 Tax gene, as shown by FACS and in situ immunohistochemistry. The authors conclude that Fab T3F2 detected the epitope/HLA-A2 complex after active and naturally occurring endogenous intracellular processing.

Reference - Authors: Yoshihisa Yamano; Cyril J Cohen; Norihiro Takenouchi; Karen Yao; Utano Tomaru; Hong-Chuan Li; Yoram Reiter; Steven Jacobson
Reference - Title: Increased expression of human T lymphocyte virus type I (HTLV-I) Tax11-19 peptide-human histocompatibility leukocyte antigen A*201 complexes on CD4+ CD25+ T Cells detected by peptide-specific, major histocompatibility complex-restricted antibodies in patients with HTLV-I-associated neurologic disease.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: The Fab Ab specific for the Tax11-19 peptide–HLA-A*0201 complex (TaxA2-Ab) is described in Cohen et al, 2003, J. Immunol. 170:4349–4361 [PMID: 12682272]. They are derived from a naive donor antibody display library.
Assay - Comments: The HLA-peptide complexes were detected with PE-labeled TaxA2-Ab and flow cytometry. The complexes were detected on peptide pulsed HmyA2.1 cells and peptide pulsed CD4+ and CD8+ cells derived from HLA-A2 healthy donors. For HAM/HSP HTLV patients, detection of endogenously processed peptide in complex with HLA-A2 was demonstrated on CD4+ T cells, but not on CD8+ T cells. Flow cytometry assay showed Tax11-19 peptide–HLA-A*201 complexes were preferentially expressed on CD4+ CD25+, CD27-, CD45RO+, CD45RA- cells (that is, in the activated, effector/memory population). The peptide was detected after 24h in vitro culture of the CD4+ cells, but not directly ex-vivo. There was a direct correlation between the level of Tax11-19 peptide–HLA-A*201 complexes detected and HTLV-I proviral DNA load, HTLV-I tax mRNA load, and HTLV Tax11-19 peptide–specific CTL frequencies.
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: Franck Kalume; Sang Min Lee; Yvette Morcos; Joseph C Callaway; Michael C Levin
Reference - Title: Molecular mimicry: cross-reactive antibodies from patients with immune-mediated neurologic disease inhibit neuronal firing.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence is found in the cited reference, Levin et al, J Infect Dis. 2002 186:1514 [PMID: 12404172].
1st immunogen - Name: transcriptional activator Tax
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Immunization - Comments: The monoclonal antibody  was obtained through the AIDS Research and Reference Reagent Program, Division of AIDS, NIAID, NIH, from Dr. Beatrice Langton.
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific mAb was added to primary neuronal cultures and it resulted in decreased neuronal firing. This is attributed to molecular mimicry to hnRNP1 expressed on neurons, as HAM/TSP patients' sera reactive to Tax protein and affinity purified on hnRNP1 caused the same responses.
Assay Antigen - Name: heterogeneous nuclear ribonucleoprotein A1 isoform a

Reference - Authors: Y Tanaka; R Tanaka; E Terada; Y Koyanagi; N Miyano-Kurosaki; N Yamamoto; E Baba; M Nakamura; H Shida
Reference - Title: Induction of antibody responses that neutralize human T-cell leukemia virus type I infection in vitro and in vivo by peptide immunization.

Epitope - Comments: The epitope was deduced.
1st immunogen - Name: PTAPPLLPHS
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 50 µg, administered at intervals of 2 months.
Immunization - Comments: The mAb was generated by fusing the spleen cells from rats immunized with the epitope with Sp2/0-Ag14 cells.
Assay - Comments: The epitope specific mAb recognized the protein by ELISA but not by Western blot.

Reference - Authors: Y Tanaka; R Tanaka; E Terada; Y Koyanagi; N Miyano-Kurosaki; N Yamamoto; E Baba; M Nakamura; H Shida
Reference - Title: Induction of antibody responses that neutralize human T-cell leukemia virus type I infection in vitro and in vivo by peptide immunization.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope was deduced.
1st immunogen - Name: PTAPPLLPHS
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 50 µg, administered at intervals of 2 months.
Immunization - Comments: The mAb was generated by fusing the spleen cells from rats immunized with the epitope with Sp2/0-Ag14 cells.
Assay - Comments: The epitope specific mAb completely inhibited HTLV-1 mediated syncytium formation at 60 ug/ml and inhibited HTLV-1 transformation of normal human T cells at 125 µg/ml.

Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope was deduced.
1st immunogen - Name: env
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 dose of 10^7 L8KSV cells infected previously with WR-proenv1 at a multiplicity of infection of 10, and 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 glycoprotein two months later.
Immunization - Comments: The mAb was generated by fusing the spleen cells from rats immunized with the epitope with Sp2/0-Ag14 cells.
Assay - Comments: The epitope specific mAb reacted with HTLV-I gp46 glycoprotein by ELISA and Western blot.

Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope was deduced.
1st immunogen - Name: env
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 dose of 10^7 L8KSV cells infected previously with WR-proenv1 at a multiplicity of infection of 10, and 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 glycoprotein two months later.

Reference - Authors: Hideki Fujii; Mamoru Shimizu; Takuya Miyagi; Marie Kunihiro; Reiko Tanaka; Yoshiaki Takahashi; Yuetsu Tanaka
Reference - Title: A Potential of an Anti-HTLV-I gp46 Neutralizing Monoclonal Antibody (LAT-27) for Passive Immunization against Both Horizontal and Mother-to-Child Vertical Infection with Human T Cell Leukemia Virus Type-I.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence was cited in Tanaka et al., J Virol. 1994 Oct;68(10):6323-31. [PMID:8083972].
1st immunogen - Name: env
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 dose of 10 MOI followed by 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 2 months later.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the monoclonal antibody was previously described in Tanaka et al., J Virol. 1994 Oct;68(10):6323-31. [PMID:8083972]. Animals were initially inoculated with L8KSV cells infected with WR-proenv1 at a multiplicity of infection of 10, and 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 glycoprotein two months later.
Assay - Comments: The humanized epitope-specific mAb blocked syncytium formation of IL-2-dependent CD4-CD8+ ILTM1 cells derived from a HTLV-1-associated myelopathy/tropical spastic paraparesis HAM/TSP patient. The original mAb, LAT-27 (IgG2b) showed similar neutralization activity.
Assay Antigen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: Hideki Fujii; Mamoru Shimizu; Takuya Miyagi; Marie Kunihiro; Reiko Tanaka; Yoshiaki Takahashi; Yuetsu Tanaka
Reference - Title: A Potential of an Anti-HTLV-I gp46 Neutralizing Monoclonal Antibody (LAT-27) for Passive Immunization against Both Horizontal and Mother-to-Child Vertical Infection with Human T Cell Leukemia Virus Type-I.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: The epitope sequence was cited in Tanaka et al., J Virol. 1994 Oct;68(10):6323-31. [PMID:8083972].
1st immunogen - Name: env
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 dose of 10 MOI followed by 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 2 months later.
Adoptive Transfer - Comments: Rattus norvegicus Sprague-Dawley were adoptively transferred with Purified Immunoglobulin.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the monoclonal antibody was previously described in Tanaka et al., J Virol. 1994 Oct;68(10):6323-31. [PMID:8083972]. Animals were initially inoculated with L8KSV cells infected with WR-proenv1 at a multiplicity of infection of 10, and 1 dose of 50 µg gp46 glycoprotein two months later.
Assay - Response measured: pathogen burden after challenge after adoptive transfer
Assay - Comments: Immunization with the humanized epitope-specific mAb protected mice from challenge with the virus. Complete protection (9/9) was also seen in the offspring of mice that received the mAb during pregnancy. In addition, humanized immunodeficient hu-PBL-NOG mice pre-infused intravenously with the epitope specific mAb were protected from HTLV-I infection.
Assay Antigen - Name: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I (Human T cell leukemia virus type 1)
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I

Reference - Authors: Guiqing Hu; Jun Liu; Kenneth H Roux; Kenneth A Taylor
Reference - Title: Structure of Simian Immunodeficiency Virus Envelope Spikes Bound with CD4 and Monoclonal Antibody 36D5.
Epitope - Reference Name: Epitope of mAb 36D5 on SIV Env
Epitope - Source Organism: Simian-Human immunodeficiency virus
Epitope - Comments: The epitope residues were calculated from [PDB: 3JCB] as the antigen residues at 4Å atomic distance from the antibody.
1st immunogen - Name: gp160 envelope glycoprotein [Simian-Human immunodeficiency virus]
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Simian-Human immunodeficiency virus
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 3 doses of 50 µg at 4-week intervals
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the monoclonal antibody was previously described in the cited reference: Edinger et al. (2000) J Virol 74(17): 7922-7935 [PMID: 10933700]. Mice were immunized intradermally with 50 μg of SIV CP-MAC soluble gp140 oligomers three times at 4-week intervals, with a final boost 4 days before hybridoma fusion. The first immunization was done in Freund's complete adjuvant; incomplete Freund's adjuvant was used for subsequent immunizations. Splenocytes from a one animal were harvested and cells were fused with SP2 myeloma cells. Hybridomas were screened for reactivity with sgp140 by ELISA. The Env protein of CP-MAC, a lab-adapted variant of SIVmacBK28, was chosen because of its highly stable gp120/gp41 association.
Assay - Comments: The epitope of mAb 36D5 on the human immunodeficiency virus type 1 (HIV-1)/simian immunodeficiency virus (SIV) envelope spike (Env) was determined by cryo-electron tomography analysis of the complex.

Epitope - Source Organism: Bovine leukemia virus
1st immunogen - Name: PDCAICWEPSPPWAPE
1st immunogen - Source Organism: Bovine leukemia virus
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 3 doses of 3 ug at 14 day intervals
Immunization - Comments: Multiple immunogens were studied all of which had the epitope conjugated to different carriers. The three investigated carriers were: a mutant bacteriophage Qβ-carrier conjugated with an N-terminus homo-bifunctional dinitrophenyl adipate linker (NPL), a mutant bacteriophage Qβ-carrier conjugated with an N-terminus isothiocyanate group (NCS), or the epitope conjugated to keyhole limpet hemocyanin.
Assay - Comments: Both mutant bacteriophage Qβ- conjugates had similar results. KHL showed a slightly lower IgG titer. IgG1, IgG2b, IgG2c, IgG3 all had similar titers. The epitope with no carriers or conjugation had IgG titers no different from negative contols. The epitope conjugated to NCS showed the strongest IgG titer at day 539 post-immunization.

1st immunogen - Source Organism: UR2 sarcoma virus

Reference - Authors: J K Wu; J K Wang
Reference - Title: Increased expression in human astrocytomas of a 100 kDa protein with sequence homology to the ros tyrosine kinase domain.
Epitope - Source Organism: UR2 sarcoma virus
1st immunogen - Name: VWETLTLGQQPYPGLSNIEVL
1st immunogen - Source Organism: UR2 sarcoma virus
Immunization - Comments: The details of the immunization procedure were not described. The mAb was purchased from Microbiological Associates, Bethesda, MD.
Assay - Comments: The epitope-specific mAb bound a protein of U-242MG glioblastoma cells measured by Western blot. In addition, high levels of a 100 kDa protein were detected in many primary brain tumors. In contrast, low levels of this 100 kDa protein were consistently found in the non-tumor brain control samples. This protein is probably not the c-ros protein but may be a novel cytosolic protein-tyrosine kinase and a marker for early transformation of astrocytomas.

Reference - Authors: Michael J Campa; Elizabeth B Gottlin; Kevin Wiehe; Edward F Patz Jr
Reference - Title: A tumor-binding antibody with cross-reactivity to viral antigens.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human endogenous retrovirus K
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the parent mAb 7968 was described in cited reference [PMID: 27160908] and patent application NCT04314089. PBMCs of 11 patients diagnosed with non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC), and who were shown by immunoblot to express CFH autoantibody, were pooled. Memory B cells were sorted from the pooled PBMCs using a biotinylated CFH 15-mer peptide containing the epitope as bait. Ig VH and VL gene pairs were isolated for expression. GT103 is the IgG3 version of mAb 7968.
Assay - Comments: The anti-CFH mAb GT103 bound the antigen which contained the core binding motif.
